{"title_page": "Alexis Ren", "text_new": "{{short description|Model}}\n{{Infobox model\n| name = Alexis Rene\n| image = Alexis_Ren.jpg\n| caption = Ren in 2017\n| birth_name = Alexis Ren\u00e9 Glabach\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|mf=yes|1996|11|23}}\n| birth_place = [[Santa Monica, California]]\n| occupation = {{hlist|Internet celebrity|model}}\n| partner= Noah Centineo\n| height = {{height|ft=5|in=7.5}}\n| hair_color = Dark Blonde\n| eye_color = Brown\n| agency = Nous Model Management<refname=\"NOUS\">{{Cit web|url=https://www.nousmodels.com/women/599452/alexis-ren/book|title=Nous Model Management - Alexis Ren Portfolio|website=www..com|access-date=2019-11-15}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''Alexis Ren\u00e9 Glabach''' (born November 23, 1994), known professionally as '''Alexis Ren''', is an American [[Internet celebrity]]<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.thecut.com/2017/05/instagram-teen-idol-alexis-ren-on-being-perfect.html|title=Instagram's Teen Idol on What It's Like to Be 'Perfect'|last=Jones|first=Allie|website=The Cut|language=en|access-date=2019-07-27}}</ref> and [[Model (person)|model]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.teenvogue.com/story/alexis-ren-maxim-cover |title=Alexis Ren Lands Her First Magazine Cover |date=July 9, 2017 |last=Weiss |first=Suzannah |work=Teen Vogue|access-date=2017-07-17 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nOn November 23, 1996, Ren was born Alexis Ren\u00e9 Glabach in [[Santa Monica]], [[California]], United States. Ren grew up in [[Santa Monica, California]]<ref name=\"maxim_ren\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.maxim.com/women/alexis-ren-august-cover-story-2017-7 |title=Alexis Ren Is ''Maxim''{{'}}s August Cover Girl |work=Maxim|access-date=2017-07-17 |language=en-us}}</ref> where she was homeschooled.<ref name = \"cosmopolitan\">{{cite web |last1=Narins |first1=Elizabeth |title=Instagram Star Alexis Ren Opens Up About the Eating Disorder She Hid for Years |url=https://www.cosmopolitan.com/health-fitness/a9657755/alexis-ren-eating-disorder/ |website=Cosmopolitan |accessdate=November 6, 2018 |date=May 25, 2017}}</ref> Ren grew up with two sisters and a younger brother.<ref name = \"cosmopolitan\"/>\n\n==Career==\nAt 13, Ren was discovered to model for the label Brandy Melville.<ref name=\"maxim_ren\"/> She became a social media phenomenon at 15, when photos of her in a black string bikini posing by the pool went viral on [[Tumblr]].<ref name=\":1\" /> Since then she has appeared in a series of advertisements for the mobile game ''[[Final Fantasy XV: A New Empire]]''.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Chapple |first1=Craig |title=MZ recruits influencer and model Alexis Ren as the face of Final Fantasy XV: A New Empire ad campaign |url=http://www.pocketgamer.biz/news/66484/mz-recruits-influencer-and-model-alexis-ren-as-the-face-of-final-fantasy-xv-a-new-empire-ad-campaign/ |accessdate=September 2, 2017 |publisher=pocketgamer.biz |date=August 25, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Friederich |first1=Brandon |title=Alexis Ren Joins Kate Upton as Latest Super Hottie to Promote Mobile Video Game |url=https://www.maxim.com/women/alexis-ren-mobile-game-ad-2017-8 |accessdate=September 2, 2017 |work=Maxim |date=August 28, 2017 |language=en-us}}</ref> She launched an [[Sportswear (activewear)|activewear]] line called Ren Active.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.sidewalkhustle.com/alexis-ren-is-launching-her-own-activewear-line/ |title=Alexis Ren is Launching Her Own Activewear Line|date=2017-05-19|work=Sidewalk Hustle|access-date=2017-07-17|language=en-US}}</ref> Ren was named a ''[[Sports Illustrated Swimsuit]]'' 2018 Rookie of the year.<ref name=\"SI\">{{cite web|url=https://www.si.com/swim-daily/2017/10/05/alexis-ren-sports-illustrated-swimsuit-2018-rookie|title=Alexis Ren is officially a Sports Illustrated Swimsuit model!|publisher=|accessdate=28 December 2017}}</ref> On September 12, 2018, Ren was announced as one of the celebrities who would compete on [[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. season 27)|season 27]] of ''[[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. TV series)|Dancing with the Stars]]''. Her professional partner was [[Alan Bersten]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.etonline.com/dancing-with-the-stars-season-27-cast-revealed-meet-the-celebs-and-their-pro-partners-109440|title='Dancing With the Stars' Season 27 Cast Revealed -- Meet the Celebs and Their Pro Partners!|work=[[Entertainment Tonight]]|first=Desiree|last=Murphy|date=September 12, 2018|accessdate=September 12, 2018}}</ref> Ren and Bersten reached the finals and came in fourth place on November 19, 2018.<ref>https://abc.go.com/shows/dancing-with-the-stars/video/vdka6488488</ref>\n\nShe was ''[[Maxim (magazine)|Maxim]]''{{'}}s [[cover girl]] for the August 2017 issue,<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.maxim.com/women/alexis-ren-bikini-video-2017-7|title=Maxim Cover Girl Alexis Ren Sizzles in Brand New Bikini Beach Videos|work=Maxim|access-date=2017-07-17|language=en-us}}</ref> ''Maxim''{{'}}s Mexico cover girl for the March 2018 issue, and ''[[Sports Illustrated Swimsuit Issue]]'' Rookie for 2018.<ref name=\"SI\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cosmopolitan.com/entertainment/celebs/a10279319/alexis-ren-maxim-magazine-cover/|title=Alexis Ren Just Landed Her First Big Magazine Cover|date=2017-07-08|work=Cosmopolitan|accessdate=2018-01-07}}</ref> She was included in [[Maxim (magazine)|''Maxim''<nowiki/>'s Hot 100]] list of Sexiest Women in the World in 2019.\n\nIn October 2019, she starred as \"Scarlet Jones\" in the music video for [[Ed Sheeran]]'s \"[[South of the Border (Ed Sheeran song)|South of the Border]]\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UPOT2tgY9QQ|title=Ed Sheeran - South of the Border (feat. Camila Cabello & Cardi B) [Official Video]|via=www.youtube.com}}</ref> Before that she's also featured in the music video for Kygo's \"[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qC_SxaXL8bs Not Ok]\".\n\n==Personal life==\nHer mother, a health nutritionist expert, died in 2014 due to [[breast cancer]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.foxnews.com/lifestyle/2017/07/07/alexis-ren-opens-up-about-her-eating-disorder-overworked-myself.html |title=Alexis Ren opens up about her eating disorder: 'I overworked myself' |last=Nolasco |first=Stephanie |date=2017-07-07 |publisher=[[Fox News]]|access-date=2017-07-17|language=en-US}}</ref> Following the death of her mother, Ren developed an eating disorder, saying she was in \"a toxic state of mind\".<ref name = \"cosmopolitan\"/> \n\nIn September 2019, it was reported that Ren was dating actor and fellow model [[Noah Centineo]]. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-news/news/noah-centineo-and-alexis-ren-are-dating/|title=FYI, Internet: Noah Centineo and Alexis Ren Are Dating|date=2019-09-27|website=Us Weekly|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-17}}</ref> Centineo publicly confirmed the relationship on January 14, 2020 via a post on his Instagram.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B7UujyeJkO5/|title=Noah on Instagram: \u201cMy dad says I look like I just finished a fight with @thenotoriousmma and lost. I say, at least one of us in this photo is gorgeous \u2764\ufe0f love\u2026\u201d|website=Instagram|language=en|access-date=2020-02-17}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Instagram|alexisren}}\n* {{Twitter|AlexisRenG}}\n* {{IMDb name|7242309}}\n\n{{2010\u20132019 Sports Illustrated Swimsuit}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ren, Alexis}}\n[[Category:1996 births]]\n[[Category:American female models]]\n[[Category:American Internet celebrities]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Santa Monica, California]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Model}}\n{{Infobox model\n| name = Alexis Ren\n| image = Alexis_Ren.jpg\n| caption = Ren in 2017\n| birth_name = Alexis Ren\u00e9 Glabach\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|mf=yes|1996|11|23}}\n| birth_place = [[Santa Monica, California]]\n| occupation = {{hlist|Internet celebrity|model}}\n| partner= Noah Centineo\n| height = {{he